    "text": "Erdős Problem #65: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. Let $G$ be a graph with $n$ vertices and $kn$ edges, and $a_1<a_2<\\cdots $ be the lengths of cycles in $G$. Is it true that\\[\\sum\\frac{1}{a_i}\\gg \\log k?\\]Is the sum $\\sum\\frac{1}{a_i}$ minimised when $G$ is a complete bipartite graph? Current best: Liu and Montgomery \\cite{LiMo20} have proved the asymptotically sharp lower bound of $\\geq (\\tfrac{1}{2}-o(1))\\log k$. Prize: no. Tags: cycles, graph theory.",
